This paper is about a novel framework for visual reasoning, which involves analyzing and understanding visual data. The paper specifically focuses on improving recognition systems beyond the limitations of current convolutional neural networks (ConvNets). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves the use of knowledge graphs and graph reasoning, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for encoding semantic relationships between classes, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the framework for robotic applications, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO).
